{"type":"Microchip CLB Synthesizer Design","version":"2.0","name":"mult3x3u_main","projectId":"580b2d45-529c-479a-956a-cae991c7d09c","creationDate":"2026-01-27T16:49:11.990Z","backendversion":"https://logic.microchip.com/","device":"PIC16F13145","documentModels":[{"type":1,"id":"d01b5a17-8613-4317-a889-49d4fd3d60cb","name":"mult3x3u","text":"/*\nMicrochip CLB Synthesizer - new Verilog file\n\nImplement your Verilog module in this file and use it elsewhere in your CLB design.\n\n// Example 1: combinatorial AND implementation:\nmodule mult3x3u (a, b, q);\n    input a, b;\n    output q;\n    assign q = a & b;\nendmodule\n\n// Example 2: clocked one-bit counter that toggles only when enabled\nmodule mult3x3u (CLK, enable, q);\n    input CLK;\n    input enable;\n    output reg q;\n    always @(posedge CLK) begin\n        if (enable) begin\n            q <= !q;\n        end\n    end\nendmodule\n\nTips for using Verilog in the CLB Synthesizer:\n  - SystemVerilog and VHDL are not supported; use Verilog-2005 only.\n  - The CLB has a single global clock which is the 'CLK' port in all Verilog modules.\n  - It is not possible to use 'always @' constructs other than 'always @(posedge CLK)'.\n*/\n\nmodule mult3x3u(a2,a1,a0,b2,b1,b0,y5,y4,y3,y2,y1,y0);\n\n    input a2,a1,a0,b2,b1,b0;\n    output y5,y4,y3,y2,y1,y0;\n\n    logic [2:0] a,b;\n    logic [5:0] y;\n\n    assign a = {a2, a1, a0};\n    assign b = {b2, b1, b0};\n    assign y = $unsigned(a) * $unsigned(b);\n    assign y5 = y[5];\n    assign y4 = y[4];\n    assign y3 = y[3];\n    assign y2 = y[2];\n    assign y1 = y[1];\n    assign y0 = y[0];\nendmodule\n"},{"type":0,"id":"6260d886-fcf1-44a4-b0b3-ed8b4e271895","name":"main","data":{"class":"GraphLinksModel","linkKeyProperty":"key","linkFromPortIdProperty":"fromPort","linkToPortIdProperty":"toPort","nodeDataArray":[{"category":"inputport","portname":"CLBSWIN6","size":"130 20","loc":"-260 -290","key":3,"settings":{}},{"category":"inputport","portname":"CLBSWIN5","size":"130 20"